File: A person lighting up a gas stove during a blackout. AFP/Damien Meyer JOHANNESBURG - It looks like we can't get rid of those candles just yet, but that doesn’t mean there isn’t light at the end of the tunnel. Eskom has scrapped Stage 6 power cuts for Friday night. READ: SA's electricity crisis | Eskom says reserves running low Instead, the utility will continue Stage 4 blackouts until 10pm. The embattled power utility says due to lower than anticipated demand, blackouts will be lowered to Stage 2 until 7am on Saturday morning. READ: SA's electricity crisis | Eskom in talks with President Ramaphosa Then Stage 4 will be implemented from 7am until 10pm on Saturday and Sunday. Eskom has thanked employees who have reported for duty following a wildcat strike. The power utility is urging South Africans to use electricity sparingly. #PowerAlert1
